          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFxUJOeouoisxBvyH7erWQceOs8zWrOC_dM8rsKZXHASSzav7VVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "My wife and I visit the David Koch building frequently for my wife\u2019s continuing medical treatments.  The lobby is a grand space with lots of chairs and a self check-in area. Plenty of staff to help you. Her doctors office is on the 4th floor. We usually also go to the second floor where they have a very nice coffee stand with sweets and a cafe with hot and cold food. Tons of nice seating to eat or just hang out and relax.  Coffee is delicious. Nice but limited breakfast buffet and a made to order omelet station.\nVery enjoyable.\nBack again on January 15 for afternoon DR appt. Then we went to have caffe at the cafe on 2nd floor but it was closed. So we got coffee and a pastry at the Starbucks branded coffee stand just after you exit the elevator. Very friendly staff. Tasty pastry and good coffee.",
