        {
          "username": "Eduela Abduramani",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "112838053028298017578",
          "user_review_count": 5,
          "user_photo_count": 4,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX65G6-AzvyctNb6alAhpB0JvwrtE1UUvbBCZF9KC4gJ9MzoCoH=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "The facility is nice and modern, but the wait times are extremely frustrating. Every time I have an ultrasound appointment here (12 floor), I arrive on time, yet I have never waited less than an hour ( one time was almost 1:30 \ud83d\ude35\u200d\ud83d\udcab\ud83d\ude35\u200d\ud83d\udcab) before being called in. It doesn\u2019t seem to matter whether my appointment is first thing in the morning or late in the day\u2014the delays are always significant. Pregnancy appointments can already be stressful, and having to wait so long at every visit only adds to that stress. I hope the scheduling process can be improved to better respect patients\u2019 time as well as their health.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT20xV2F6aDZNM1JwVjI1dWEwMWpSR0p4Ym5SSlQzYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm1Wazh6M3RpV25ua01jRGJxbnRJT3c%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a week ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-06-11T23:53:11+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Melissa Marinello",
          "rating": 2,
          "contributor_id": "104815078906007577992",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW04rBgcQ8pTCosAJ6Ev7qupleoUlTvryKFSlIIolyYRZONX4Fl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Facility is nice and new, but I have never waited less than 40 minutes to be seen for an appointment that I have been ON TIME for (pregnancy scans). I\u2019m writing this after arriving for an appointment an hour ago\u2026 I have never met with a doctor who has provided more feedback than \u201ceverything looks good, any questions?\u201d The prenatal care is so bare minimum. I had my first baby at Lenox Hill up the street, and received much more thorough prenatal care. Further, people at the front desk (on 12th floor) have never been very helpful or friendly. This location is always packed.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2trMVpHNHdTbHB4YTNNMmMyVmlRa2RFY20xSmNsRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkk1ZG4wSlpxa3M2c2ViQkdEcm1JclE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "6 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-12-08T17:32:40+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Rita N.",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "103262581699815270095",
          "user_review_count": 21,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-H4jFZ8QO1sKwFbBIoFCd2D-Dhmb3F3z9EDtcKurn-S_Glg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Just had an absolutely horrible experience with the staff. Doctor and Anesthestiologists were fine but the nurses on the 8th floor were scary.  When have you ever left a hospital and not gotten after care instructions?  I was waiting to be discharged and the nurse  asked why was I still there.  She said we don't do that anymore, everything is on the portal.  Well nothing is on my portal.\nIn addition, the lack of respect for my private medical condition with the nurses calling up and down the hall about my issues and associated problem was the most horrifying experience I have ever had.  All the other patients were in hearing distance. Shameful.\nI have been getting the best medical care at  Weill Cornell/NY Presbyterian for most of my life.  This is unacceptable.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xOUE1rVTRXVkpOTjBZdFpGWjZRM2Q0U1MxdVdGRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlNPMkU4WVJNN0YtZFZ6Q3d4SS1uWFE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "6 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-12-12T01:00:04+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Aneta Trenkoska",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "116610782882988652653",
          "user_review_count": 7,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpNl_ObWhZXEF_ZW173hTmntzHva0WhboIVy3Uoi6UQfHagw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I had a very upsetting experience today at the front desk during my recent visit. The receptionist I interacted with was abrupt, dismissive, and spoke in a tone that added unnecessary stress to an already emotional situation.\nWe  do not come to hospitals casually. We are often there because we are worried, scared, and waiting for news about a dear family member. In moments like that, kindness and basic respect matter more than ever. The front desk is the face of the hospital and it should be a place of professionalism and empathy, not another source of anxiety. I hope hospital leadership takes this feedback seriously and ensures that front-desk staff are trained to meet patients with compassion, not hostility.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xaaE9VZHBNa0YyVFVWbmNYZDFlWFIyYjFwU1JuYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlZhOUdpMkF2TUVncXd1eXR2b1pSRnc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-02-02T19:21:15+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Claire Elliot",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "113506425871211564571",
          "user_review_count": 8,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUK1iboF5Ly-KAvqkd64enbuf4vozBDVlzHlzMNRv8lowjlE0s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Read all the negative reviews. The lobby is uninviting--especially when you are checking in for major procedure or have other important health issues going on. Who needs go through process that makes you do all the work and seems to be modeled on airline check-in? Doesn't the hospital want to treat its (paying) patients as humans? Or are we data entry clerks? I had to figure all of this out in a weakened state as I was arriving for colonoscopy. During another visit, I had to help a friend who was very ill figure it out. Don't put your patients through this!  There are many employees there, ostensibly to help you navigate the process, but many are busy carrying on personal conversations. However, there are a few who will walk over to you if they see you struggling.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tONlUySlZURXhtVVVaSU5VcEZkSGQyTFhOU01FRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkN6U2JVTExmUUZINUpFdHd2LXNSMEE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-01-28T00:44:21+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Tam K",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "108092347579593266697",
          "user_review_count": 3,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL-ppIjwRWiEurZ-FU1G2kUvVZhANMxNvyLPTpQigVBeJYJ6g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I\u2019m very disappointed with my experience at NewYork-Presbyterian Hospital. They made serious errors with my newborn\u2019s paperwork, and despite multiple attempts to resolve it, no one took responsibility or offered meaningful help. The patient advocate was also unresponsive and unhelpful throughout the process.\n\nFuture parents \u2014 make sure all your administrative forms and discharge paperwork are completely accurate before you leave the hospital. Once you\u2019re out, getting any assistance is nearly impossible. It\u2019s unacceptable that a hospital of this caliber provides such poor support for new families.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25WWU9WTXRiamRWUTJkWGNVSmtURk5MWmtsUlNGRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnVYOVMtbjdVQ2dXcUJkTFNLZklRSFE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "6 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-12-11T16:34:23+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Bernie Crowl",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "112348315413743523939",
          "user_review_count": 66,
          "user_photo_count": 17,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRsg_QoI0QUW-6AQHhCwyzDCyDTH6HvAM6heeT55IUtpFNBUEl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Came here to have a minor procedure and left with zero complaints! Everyone there was really kind from the moment I walked in to the second I left. The nurses and doctors were very communicative and were only there for 4 hours! It was also a pretty facility! Really amazing and highly recommend to anyone needing abdominal surgery.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xKUVZsSlNSM0ZSVGtsdWVHTkNVMWRRT0VsMExVRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa77d43b304bfcda8!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlJQVlJSR3FRTklueGNCU1dQOEl0LUE%7C%7C?hl=en",
